AMENDMENT IV
TO THE CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS
OF THE
LOWER SIOUX INDIAN COMMUNITY

 
 Article III - Membership

Section 4. The Community Council may make ordinances governing the acquisition of 
membership that will strictly adhere to the requirements of this Article.

Section 5. Disenrollments are expressly prohibited unless the enrolled member 
personally relinquishes their membership by providing written notice to the 
Community Council.

Having been duly adopted and approved, the proposed Amendment A is hereby 
designated as Amendment Number IV to the Constitution and Bylaws of the Lower 
Sioux Indian Community in Minnesota.
 
 

CERTIFICATE OF APPROVAL

 
 I, Terrance Virden, Regional Director, Midwest Regional Office, Bureau of Indian 
Affairs, by virtue of the authority granted to the Secretary of the Interior by the Act 
of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended, and further delegated to me by 3 IAM 
4.4, do hereby approve Amendment A, adopted by a vote of more than 30% of the 
qualified voters, and now designated as “Amendment Number IV”, to the 
Constitution and Bylaws of the Lower Sioux Indian Community in Minnesota. This 
amendment is effective as of this date: PROVIDED, that nothing in this approval shall 
be construed as authorizing any action that would be contrary to Federal law.

(Sgd)
Terrance L. Virden
Regional Director
Midwest Regional Office 
Bureau of Indian Affairs

